#. type: Title ###
#: ../src/docs/books/admin_guide/03-commands.md:201
#, no-wrap
msgid "`shutdown` command"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/books/admin_guide/03-commands.md:204
#, no-wrap
msgid "The `shutdown` command allows you to **electronically shut down** a Linux server, either immediately or after a certain period of time.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Fenced code block (bash)
#: ../src/docs/books/admin_guide/03-commands.md:205
#, no-wrap
msgid "shutdown [-h] [-r] time [message]\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/books/admin_guide/03-commands.md:210
#, no-wrap
msgid "Specify the shutdown time in the format `hh:mm` for a precise time, or `+mm` for a delay in minutes.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/books/admin_guide/03-commands.md:212
#, no-wrap
msgid "To force an immediate stop, use the word `now` in place of the time. In this case, the optional message is not sent to other users of the system.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Fenced code block (bash)
#: ../src/docs/books/admin_guide/03-commands.md:215
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"[root]# shutdown -h 0:30 \"Server shutdown at 0:30\"\n"
"[root]# shutdown -r +5\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/books/admin_guide/03-commands.md:221
#: ../src/docs/guides/security/pam.md:238
#: ../src/docs/labs/security/lab9-cryptography.md:594
#, no-wrap
msgid "Options:\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/books/admin_guide/03-commands.md:226
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"| Options | Remarks                          |\n"
"| ------- | -------------------------------- |\n"
"| `-h`    | Shuts down the system electronically. |\n"
"| `-r`    | Restarts the system.              |\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ###
#: ../src/docs/books/admin_guide/03-commands.md:227
#, no-wrap
msgid "`history` command"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/books/admin_guide/03-commands.md:230
#, no-wrap
msgid "The `history` command displays the history of commands that have been entered by the user.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/books/admin_guide/03-commands.md:232
#, no-wrap
msgid "The commands are stored in the `.bash_history` file in the user's login directory.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/books/admin_guide/03-commands.md:234
#, no-wrap
msgid "Example of a history command\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Fenced code block (bash)
#: ../src/docs/books/admin_guide/03-commands.md:235
#, no-wrap
